> Instead of Bondo which soaks up moisture and leads
> to rust - - - get a 
> gallon of metal impregnated filler.
> 
> The brand name I have used is "Metal to Metal". It
> is a bondo like material 
> full of ground up aluminum. It is waterproof and
> much harder stuff. We have 
> used it to seal Swiss cheese floors with good
> results. (Structurally it was 
> solid with many little holes, full frame car).
